"{\"uid\": \"velo.outsideonline.com-olympics-key-takeaways-2024-olympic-mens-road-race\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Powered byOutside  PARIS, FRANCE - AUGUST 03: Gold medalist Remco Evenepoel of Team Belgium poses on the podium with his gold medals of Individual Time Trial and Road race during the Men's Road Race on day eight of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 at trocadero on August 03, 2024 in Paris, France.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 32, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.498395531651183e-17, \"text\": \"PARIS, FRANCE\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 32, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.498395531651183e-17, \"text\": \"PARIS, FRANCE\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 60, \"end\": 75, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}, {\"begin\": 84, \"end\": 91, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999996312054235, \"rank\": 3.687948129934768e-07, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 136, \"end\": 157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Individual_time_trial\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1173768422599448e-97, \"text\": \"Individual Time Trial\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Individual_time_trial\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Individual_time_trial\"}, {\"begin\": 279, \"end\": 284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0374612444409026e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 286, \"end\": 292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9057705562994187, \"rank\": 0.10381642054483313, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by Jared C. Tilton/Getty Images)  With a jaw-dropping display of pure power, speed, and a perfectly timed attack,Remco Evenepoelwon the men's 2024 Olympic road race andcompleted a historic time trial/road race gold medal doubleafter riding clear of an elite group of favorites on the picturesque yet chaotic Parisian city circuit.\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 631, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tilton_on_the_Hill\", \"score\": 0.9999999443689391, \"rank\": 5.5631158059477033e-08, \"text\": \"Tilton\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tilton_on_the_Hill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tilton_on_the_Hill\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind him, the French duo of Valentin Madouas and Christophe Laporte pulled off the impressive feat of filling out the remaining podium places, with Madouas just barely holding on after being dropped by Evenepoel's winning assault and Laporte working over the chase group behind in the slow-speed sprint.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6300102675393169, \"rank\": 0.5743133257853111, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 665, \"end\": 681, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valentin Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christophe Laporte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\"}, {\"begin\": 785, \"end\": 792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have broken down the key takeaways from the memorable race through the streets of Paris below.\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1026, \"end\": 1031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0374612444409026e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris Olympic Road Race 2024 Top 101)Remco Evenepoel (Belgium) +02)Valentin Madouas (France) +1'113)Christophe Laporte (France) +1'164)Attila Valter (Hungary) +1'165)Toms Skuji\\u0146\\u0161 (Latvia) +1'166)Marco Haller (Austria) +1'167)Stefan K\\u00fcng (Switzerland) +1'168)Jan Tratnik (Slovenia) +1'169)Matteo Jorgenson (United States) +1'1610)Ben Healy (Ireland) +1'20  270km-128.4km to go: With such a long course and small field, the teams of the favorites let an early breakaway go up the road and build up a massive advantage before putting key riders on the front to chisel the gap back down after roughly 100kms of racing.\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1654, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1077, \"end\": 1092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}, {\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999996312054235, \"rank\": 3.687948129934768e-07, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 1125, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9057705562994187, \"rank\": 0.10381642054483313, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1140, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christophe Laporte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\"}, {\"begin\": 1160, \"end\": 1166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9057705562994187, \"rank\": 0.10381642054483313, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {