\"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.5933863547611286, \"rank\": 0.6642844632404654, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In between, a chase group, including Ireland's Ryan Mullen, clearly a satellite rider for an eventual Ben Healy attack, are bridging up to the front.\", \"from\": 1655, \"to\": 1804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1692, \"end\": 1699, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.5933863547611286, \"rank\": 0.6642844632404654, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 1702, \"end\": 1713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Mullen\", \"score\": 0.9999964357339051, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryan Mullen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Mullen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Mullen\"}, {\"begin\": 1757, \"end\": 1766, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.158380119818449e-25, \"text\": \"Ben Healy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably, the four-rider French team is sitting back and refusing to use precious resources at this point, while the three-rider Dutch team uses a key rider, Dan Hoole.\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1972, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1835, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6300102675393169, \"rank\": 0.5743133257853111, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1933, \"end\": 1938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999943073269749, \"rank\": 2.7856647249293487e-06, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"88km: As the race enters the outskirts of Paris, Alexey Lutsenko attacks, realizing that everyone but the ultra-top tier favorites will need to get in front of the race before they enter the city circuit.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2178, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2016, \"end\": 2021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0374612444409026e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2023, \"end\": 2038, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexey_Lutsenko\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexey Lutsenko\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexey_Lutsenko\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexey_Lutsenko\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is followed by Healy, whose teammate Mullen is now just 90 seconds up the road and sitting up to wait for Healy.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2294, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2219, \"end\": 2225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"score\": 0.9965110546188849, \"rank\": 0.0035011352991297187, \"text\": \"Mullen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Mullen_Jr.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"67.4km:Remco Evenepoel unleashes one of a handful of early attacks on a flat section of road through a feed zone.\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2305, \"end\": 2320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is quickly marked by USA's Matteo Jorgenson and a handful of others, but this is likely just an attempt to soften up the group and gauge how much strength the thin Dutch team still has at this point.\", \"from\": 2412, \"to\": 2614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2436, \"end\": 2439, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997372679336, \"rank\": 2.0926126872654212e-07, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2442, \"end\": 2458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Jorgenson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\"}, {\"begin\": 2579, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999943073269749, \"rank\": 2.7856647249293487e-06, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"60km:After entering Paris, with Ben Healy still pushing 30 seconds off the front, Germany's Nils Politt takes advantage of the pace, finally coming off on the front by ripping clear with a strong attack.\", \"from\": 2618, \"to\": 2821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2638, \"end\": 2643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0374612444409026e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.158380119818449e-25, \"text\": \"Ben Healy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ben_Healy\"}, {\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.8967513812188755, \"rank\": 0.11435529415292213, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 2710, \"end\": 2714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nil_Desperandum_GAA\", \"score\": 0.9989852659960935, \"rank\": 0.000929754678091718, \"text\": \"Nils\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nil_Desperandum_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nil_Desperandum_GAA\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"59.3km:Back in the peloton, the still-slow pace allows riders to stream across the gap.\", \"from\": 2825, \"to\": 2912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eventually, a strong group, including France's Valentin Madouas and Switzerland's Stefan K\\u00fcng, formed.\", \"from\": 2913, \"to\": 3015, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2951, \"end\": 2957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9057705562994187, \"rank\": 0.10381642054483313, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valentin Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 2981, \"end\": 2992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9999524156754287, \"rank\": 3.2280933061915826e-05, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 2995, \"end\": 3006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_K\\u00fcng\", \"score\": 0.9999998054609212, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefan K\\u00fcng\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_K\\u00fcng\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefan_K\\u00fcng\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Belgium gets back on the front to control the gap, but with no representation in the front group and only a fatigued Tiesj Benoot left to set the pace, this is a precarious situation for the race's dominant team.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3228, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999996312054235, \"rank\": 3.687948129934768e-07, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}, {\"begin\": 3133, \"end\": 3145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiesj_Benoot\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tiesj Benoot\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiesj_Benoot\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiesj_Benoot\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"46km:When they hit the cobbled climb of Butte Montmartre, with Healy still solo, the peloton 40 seconds behind the strong chase group, and Belgium having no domestiques left to reel in them, Mathieu van der Poel attacks and is immediately followed by Wout Van Aert and a small group of elite riders who ride clear.\", \"from\": 3232, \"to\": 3546, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3278, \"end\": 3288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.414312401541311e-21, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}, {\"begin\": 3423, \"end\": 3443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathieu van der Poel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\"}, {\"begin\": 3423, \"end\": 3443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mathieu van der Poel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mathieu_van_der_Poel\"}, {\"begin\": 3483, \"end\": 3496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wout Van Aert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"38.6km:This escape group, which is mainly being driven by Van der Poel and Jorgenson, is eventually reeled in by Mads Pedersen, who missed it due to an ill-timed flat, with the peloton following closely behind.\", \"from\": 3550, \"to\": 3760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3663, \"end\": 3676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9973584045699821, \"rank\": 0.0026481297583575304, \"text\": \"Mads Pedersen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably, France's Julian Alaphilippe was able to mark the move and sit on to de-incentivize the chase for his teammate Madouas.\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3770, \"end\": 3776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9057705562994187, \"rank\": 0.10381642054483313, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3779, \"end\": 3797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Julian Alaphilippe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\"}, {\"begin\": 3880, \"end\": 3887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"38km:As soon as the groups combine, with Van der Poel sitting near the front marking Van Aert, Remco Evenepoel sees the perfect opportunity and launches a perfectly timed attack.\", \"from\": 3892, \"to\": 4070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3987, \"end\": 4002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"38km:Unlike his previous attacks, Evenepoel's move immediately opens up significant daylight due to the group being gassed from the just-completed chase.\", \"from\": 4072, \"to\": 4225, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Evenepoel is able to quickly bridge up to the chase group, which is now just 11 seconds ahead, while Healy is still impressively alone on the front.\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"27.8km:On the second pass of Butte Montmartre, with Evenepoel ripping through the front groups and the peloton now 45 seconds behind him, Van der Poel attacks again.\", \"from\": 4378, \"to\": 4543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4413, \"end\": 4423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.414312401541311e-21, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, he is again closely marked by Van Aert, who refuses to pull through due to his 'teammate' being up the road.\", \"from\": 4544, \"to\": 4661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At this point, with Evenepoel off the front, Van der Poel unable to shake Van Aert, and Van Aert showing he is here to support his national team, the race is essentially over.\", \"from\": 4662, \"to\": 4837, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"21.5km:Up front, after hurricane Evenepoel has ripped through the groups, the only rider remaining on his wheel is Madouas.\", \"from\": 4841, \"to\": 4964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4956, \"end\": 4963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even though Madouas is sitting behind Evenepoel, the difference in the two riders' aerodynamic positions means that Madouas is struggling to get a draft.\", \"from\": 4965, \"to\": 5118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4977, \"end\": 4984, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 5081, \"end\": 5088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With 44 seconds on the Van der Poel peloton and knowing he can drop Madouas at will, Evenepoel has settled into a relatively controlled pace.\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5187, \"end\": 5194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"15km:On the next climb up to the top of the course in Montmartre, Evenepoel simply turns up the pace and leaves Madouas in his wake.\", \"from\": 5264, \"to\": 5396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5318, \"end\": 5328, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.414312401541311e-21, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}, {\"begin\": 5376, \"end\": 5383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Madouas, to his credit, realizes resistance is futile and immediately sits down to focus on keeping his own pace high in an attempt to hold off the chase behind to salvage a medal placing.\", \"from\": 5397, \"to\": 5585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5397, \"end\": 5404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3.8km:Heading through the Louvre and toward the finish along the Seine, Evenepoel suffers an extremely ill-timed flat time, which sets off a panicked bike change.\", \"from\": 5589, \"to\": 5751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5615, \"end\": 5621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.999999972249498, \"rank\": 2.7750126925231582e-08, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}, {\"begin\": 5654, \"end\": 5659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4231031325741708e-26, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While he has 1'31 on the peloton and 1'15 on Madouas (who is still fighting to hold off the chase), Evenepoel has no way of knowing his lead is relatively safe due to the lack of race radios.\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 5943, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5797, \"end\": 5804, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finish:After getting back up to speed, Evenepoel crosses the finish line, set spectacularly in front of the Eiffel Tower, and, in true showman fashion, poses for a clearly pre-planned photo-op to celebrate his historic TT/RR double gold performance.\", \"from\": 5947, \"to\": 6196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6166, \"end\": 6168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"score\": 0.9999999999845386, \"rank\": 1.5657918658629707e-11, \"text\": \"TT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Isle_of_Man_TT\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chase Group Finish:Just over a minute behind, Madouas polishes off an incredible ride to hold on for silver, while his French teammate, Christophe Laporte, who has marked Matteo Jorgenson's attempts to bridge across through the final few laps, wins the sprint for third.\", \"from\": 6200, \"to\": 6470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6246, \"end\": 6253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 6319, \"end\": 6325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6300102675393169, \"rank\": 0.5743133257853111, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 6336, \"end\": 6354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christophe Laporte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\"}, {\"begin\": 6371, \"end\": 6387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Jorgenson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To highlight the chaos of the race, Laporte, who finished third, did not realize he had finished on the podium, while fourth place, Attila Valter, celebrated thinking he had finished third.\", \"from\": 6471, \"to\": 6660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6603, \"end\": 6616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila_Valter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Attila Valter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila_Valter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Attila_Valter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1) The Unusually Small Field Perfectly Suited Remco Evenepoel's Attacking Style:The 24-year-old Belgian became the first male rider to complete the Olympic time trial and road race double with a trademark solo victory where instead of using layers of tactics and deception, he simply rode everyone off his wheel until he crossed the finish line for a major solo victory.\", \"from\": 6664, \"to\": 7034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6760, \"end\": 6767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999704969018, \"rank\": 2.9503064565917505e-08, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"2) Mathieu van der Poel's Aggressive Tactics Played Right Into Belgium's Hands:After coming into the race as a near-absurd pre-race favorite, the World Champion quickly put his team to work on the front before launching an attack once the race hit the Butte Montmartre, the hardest part of the Parisian circuit.\", \"from\": 7036, \"to\": 7347, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7182, \"end\": 7196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"score\": 0.9400405245317768, \"rank\": 0.06366367713924581, \"text\": \"World Champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_championship\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately, he was duly marked by his lifelong rival, Wout van Aert, and, with other top favorites like Denmark's Mads Pedersen having no intention of letting a dual-superstar move ride clear, the duo quickly had company.\", \"from\": 7348, \"to\": 7572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7405, \"end\": 7418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wout van Aert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\"}, {\"begin\": 7455, \"end\": 7462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.9974182975841969, \"rank\": 0.0025883848524892268, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 7465, \"end\": 7478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9973584045699821, \"rank\": 0.0026481297583575304, \"text\": \"Mads Pedersen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mads_Pedersen_(cyclist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"3) The Hometown French Squad's Ultra-Pragmatic Racing Paid Off Perfectly:While the Dutch, Danish, and Belgian teams burned precious resources early in the race, controlling the gap to the early breakaway, the French, even with a strong four-rider team (the maximum allowable number), sat back and allowed their competitors to chase before unleashing a classic 'punt and squeeze' tactic that saw them sweep up the only two realistic podium spots.\", \"from\": 7574, \"to\": 8019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7581, \"end\": 7589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancestral_home_(Chinese)\", \"score\": 0.5861652865887818, \"rank\": 0.34580216126350805, \"text\": \"Hometown\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancestral_home_(Chinese)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancestral_home_(Chinese)\"}, {\"begin\": 7590, \"end\": 7602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999946816301871, \"rank\": 5.318397664570617e-06, \"text\": \"French Squad\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7657, \"end\": 7662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999943073269749, \"rank\": 2.7856647249293487e-06, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 7664, \"end\": 7670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.9999999963374648, \"rank\": 2.3083604443559893e-09, \"text\": \"Danish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}, {\"begin\": 7676, \"end\": 7683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9999999704969018, \"rank\": 2.9503064565917505e-08, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"4) Behind the National Team Lineups, Two Trade Teams Had Big Days:One of the most interesting quirks of International racing (Olympics, Worlds & Continental Championships) is that riders who are paid incredibly well to work for one another 364 days of the year are suddenly thrust into the roles of rivals while riders who are fierce rivals (e.g., Van Aert & Evenepoel), are placed in the roles of teammates.\", \"from\": 8021, \"to\": 8429, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While Saturday's Road Race did not produce as many of the usual 'secret teammate' shenanigans that we have seen in the past (where trade teammates work for one another despite being on different national teams), it is interesting to look at how many riders each trade team placed in the top ten.\", \"from\": 8430, \"to\": 8725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"5)International Courses Are Always More Difficult In Practice Than They Appear on Paper:While it would have been easy to look at the course and envision a Milano-Sanremo-type outcome, without the benefit of massive teams deep with firepower, the small pelotons inevitably break up due to constant attacks before the finish line.\", \"from\": 8729, \"to\": 9057, \"entities\": []}]}"